</footer>



    <section class="po-hr-cn prt-y">

      <h1 class="po-hr-cn__title">&#8220;We&#8217;re Fighting a Mean-Spirited and Antidemocratic Attack on Public Education&#8221;</h1>

      <div class="po-hr-cn__contributors">
        <dl class="po-hr-cn__authors">
          
            
              <dt class="po-hr-cn__byline">An interview with</dt>
            
            
          
          
            <dd class="po-hr-cn__author">
              <a class="po-hr-cn__author-link" href="/author/tim-marshall">Tim Marshall</a>
            </dd>
          
        </dl>
        
          
        
      </div>

      <p class="po-hr-cn__dek">Oakland teachers aren’t just fighting for a living wage and better working conditions. They’re fighting against the closure of dozens of schools, which would pave the way for the privatization and destruction of public education.</p>
    </section>

    

    
      
        <figure class="po-hr-im prt-x">
          
            
            

            <img alt class="po-hr-im__image" height="899" src="https://images.jacobinmag.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/22150250/joe-brusky.jpeg" width="1600"/>

            
              
                <figcaption class="po-hr-im__caption">
                  <p class="po-hr-im__description">Oakland teachers on strike on February 21, 2019. Joe Brusky</p>
                </figcaption>
              
            
          
        </figure>

      
    

</header>


        

          <div class="po__container">

            









            <div class="po__main prt-y">

